# ========================================================================
# tmuxd SERVER configuration
# ========================================================================
#
# This file configures a tmuxd SERVER (the box running `npm start`).
# Outbound CLIENT machines that expose their local tmux to this server use
# a different template — see .env.client.example.
#
# tmuxd uses a TWO-TOKEN trust model — see docs/identity-model.md.
#
#   1. Server token (this file): the trust-circle key. Anyone who knows
#      it can use this server. Configure it here on the server; every
#      web/CLI/client presents it on connect.
#
#   2. User token (per-user, NOT in this file): each user invents or
#      generates one personal token and keeps it private. The server
#      does NOT store user tokens; it derives
#      namespace = sha256(userToken).slice(0, 16) and uses that as the
#      user's identity tag.
#
# Add a user → tell them the server token (1) and have them generate or
# pick a user token (2). No server-side config change needed for new
# users or new clients.
# ========================================================================
#
# Pick a deployment mode (full guide: docs/deployment-modes.md):
#
#   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
#   │ Want anyone besides yourself to use this server?                │
#   │ ├── No  → Mode A: HOST=127.0.0.1, leave TMUXD_RELAY unset       │
#   │ └── Yes → Should this box itself host tmux sessions?            │
#   │           ├── Yes → Mode B: HOST=0.0.0.0, TMUXD_RELAY unset     │
#   │           │        (server's local tmux is visible to ALL users)│
#   │           └── No  → Mode C: HOST=0.0.0.0, TMUXD_RELAY=1 ⭐      │
#   │                     (relay mode — recommended multi-user shape) │
#   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
# How widely to share the server token (1Password / signup gate /
# README) is an OPERATIONAL choice, not a separate mode. The server
# behaves identically regardless. See "Distributing the server token"
# in docs/deployment-modes.md.
# ========================================================================

# Required: shared trust-circle token. Treat like a team password.
# Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
TMUXD_SERVER_TOKEN=change-me

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Relay mode
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When TMUXD_RELAY=1, the server refuses to host tmux sessions itself
# (every local route returns 403; the local host is hidden from every
# namespace). Operators run clients from elsewhere; the server is purely
# a routing layer. Recommended for any multi-user deployment.
# TMUXD_RELAY=1

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Network
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Bind address. 127.0.0.1 = local only (default). 0.0.0.0 = all NICs.
HOST=127.0.0.1

# HTTP port.
PORT=7681

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
# JWT secret
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auto-generated and persisted to .tmuxd/jwt-secret if not set.
# Override only if you need to share JWT-signing keys across multiple
# server replicas behind a load balancer.
# JWT_SECRET=

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Audit log
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Structured single-line JSON on stderr. Events: login_success,
# login_failure, auth_failure, client_register, client_rejected,
# client_disconnect, ws_attach. Set this only for tests that want
# clean stderr — production should leave it on.
# TMUXD_AUDIT_DISABLE=1

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
# tmux binary
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Override the tmux binary the local-tmux paths invoke.
# Useful for hosts where tmux is at a non-standard location.
# TMUXD_TMUX_PATH=/opt/tmux/bin/tmux
